      • getResource

        default GridFsResource getResource(String location)
        从接口复制的说明: ResourceLoader
        Return a Resource handle for the specified resource location.

        The handle should always be a reusable resource descriptor,

        • Must support fully qualified URLs, e.g. "file:C:/test.dat".
        • Must support classpath pseudo-URLs, e.g. "classpath:test.dat".
        • Should support relative file paths, e.g. "WEB-INF/test.dat". (This will be implementation-specific, typically provided by an ApplicationContext implementation.)

        Note that a Resource handle does not imply an existing resource;

        指定者:
        getResource 在接口中 ResourceLoader
        参数:
        location - the resource location
        返回:
        a corresponding Resource handle (never null)
        另请参阅:
        ResourceLoader.CLASSPATH_URL_PREFIX

      • getResources

        default GridFsResource[] getResources(String filenamePattern)
        从接口复制的说明: ResourcePatternResolver
        Resolve the given location pattern into Resource objects.

        Overlapping resource entries that point to the same physical resource should be avoided, as far as possible. The result should have set semantics.

        指定者:
        getResources 在接口中 ResourcePatternResolver
        参数:
        filenamePattern - the location pattern to resolve
        返回:
        the corresponding Resource objects
